Candidate of Social Democratic Party (SDP), Engineer Segun Oni cast his vote at Unit 6 Ward 2 Uro, Ifaki at exactly 10:22 am along with his wife, Kemi. Although, accreditation at the voting centre started slowly but it later picked up. There was massive turn out of voters who patiently waited on the queue to case their vote. Among the voters was a 105 years old Mama Felicia Fayomi, who was accompanied by one of her grandchild. There are also aged disabled who came out to exercise their franchise, saying, their determination was to vote for change in Ekiti State in the next four years. While addressing the media, Oni alleged there was voting buying in Ado and Oye Ekiti. He therefore urged security agents and other necessary should step in to stop the shenanigan. 